Call of Duty: Modern Warfare 2,"Some say that the newer CoD games have ruined a decade of gaming; and they wouldn't be wrong either. But what's that? Peaking through the clouds in a radiant beam of light and glory, oh my God, it's Modern Warfare 2!  Modern Warfare 2 was my favorite CoD game and also was the one that really got me involved in the shooter genre. I loved this game and I still do! There were so many aspects that made this game right and actually enjoyable. The planets had alligned over Infinity Ward and they took that oppertunity.  The music (Composed by HANS ZIMMER) helped provide the tune and emotion of the scenery. No sounds felt out of place. The weapons all had their buffs and debuffs making some better adapted to certain situations than others. The story was rememberable and actually had me immersed in the experience that was Modern Warfare 2. The Task Force missions were things from action movie and kept doing something new each time. The Rangers started with what looked like actual combat scenarios in the middle east and transitioned over to defending the US from oncoming attacks in suburban areas and D.C. The Characters were likeable and all fit their postions nicely and the game left an amazing cliffhanger that was flopped by 2011's catastrophy: Modern Warfare 3.  This game had ties to the first that could be over looked without playing the prequel before this one, but not enough that the entire game makes no sense. The game had one of the most intense controversial moments that did nothing but increase interest in the game. The only three faults were 1. The constant hackers in the early days of the Multiplayer 2. Beating a dead horse with killing off characters again 3. The Favela controversy and the removal from the map rotation.  Possible one of the best CoDs ever and very easy to recommend."
