Call of Duty: Modern Warfare 2,"SP: The story is nothing special, in my opinion. It continues where it's predecessor left off in Call of Duty 4. Not to say that the story itself is bad, but it's nothing different than what you see in any other COD title. It is interesting enough to keep me engaged for as long as I'm willing to play, along with fun easter eggs and those sort of things. The characters, for the most part, are well thought out. Enough so that I became begrudgingly attached after playing beginning to end so many times. All in all, a solid title with a solid campaign.   MP: Obviously the highlight of most COD titles is the multiplayer, and it's no different for MW2. However, MW2's fifteen minutes of fame -- and support -- has long since gone by. Multiplayer, now, is largely dead. There's not many players online, and you do encounter the occasional hacker. Although I played a few games the other day without a hacker in sight. Even so, there 's approximately five game modes available, only two of which have enough players to run more than one game at a time. Still I have to give props to the PC MW2 crowd. Multiplayer has been dead for years on the console, but the PC version is still coughing up blood.   PC Port: The PC port is surprisingly good. The controls are spot on -- I had to configure mine a bit -- making it feel very natural and very easy to play on a PC. The same could not be said of Black Ops which had a terrible PC port (Up there with Dead Space). Graphics settings are robust enough, but not overwhelming - although it is quite bad at detecting optimal settings automatically. Handles everything just as well, if not better than, the consoles.   SP: 7/10 MP: 7/10 Overall: 8.5/10"
